mlxcel (0.2.0-1~jammy1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Added: unified paged KV cache is live in the batching server (epic
    #116). Prefix reuse and paged block storage now run together: a shared
    prefix is stored once with reference counting and copy-on-write, so a
    second request adopts the existing blocks and re-prefills only its
    divergent suffix. Pool-backed decode is byte-identical to the dense
    path on qwen3 and llama3 (#152, #167, #168).
  * Added: disaggregated serving. `mlxcel-server --node-role
    {prefill,decode,router}` with --serving-bind, --prefill-peers, and
    --decode-peers splits prefill, decode, and a model-free router across
    processes over TCP; a 3-process run is byte-identical to a single
    hybrid node. KV block contents serialize across the handoff
    (#185, #187, #188, #189, #190, #191, #192, #193).
  * Added: DiffusionGemma block-diffusion model: text generation, image
    input, and mlxcel-server serving. Temperature-0 output is
    byte-identical across the MLX bump (#217, #218, #219, #220).
  * Added: Qwen3-Coder XML tool-call parsing, surfaced as OpenAI tool_calls
    (#206).
  * Added: --kv-cache-budget <BYTES|auto> (env MLXCEL_KV_CACHE_BUDGET) caps
    the paged KV block pool with an admission gate and cold-prefix eviction;
    opt-in, unbounded by default. Paged usage is exposed at
    GET /v1/cache/stats and on /metrics (#174, #175, #176, #178).
  * Added: architecture-aware KV-cache memory estimation for inspect and
    the --estimate-memory preflight, plus an explicit activation term.
    Sliding-window, MLA, hybrid, and pure-SSM models no longer use a flat
    formula that was off by about 100x for Gemma, DeepSeek, and Mamba
    (#172, #173).
  * Added (opt-in): VLM prompt-prefix cache sharing for multi-turn
    same-image conversations behind --enable-vlm-prefix-cache, verified
    byte-identical to a cold prefill on qwen2-vl-2b (#182, #184).
  * Added: fused paged-attention decode Metal kernel (split-K
    flash-decoding), gated off because it does not beat MLX gather-then-SDPA
    at long context on Apple Silicon. Enable with
    MLXCEL_PAGED_ATTENTION_NATIVE (#181).
  * Changed: Automatic Prefix Caching is now enabled by default; the output
    is unchanged (#233).
  * Changed: the prompt-prefix KV cache now serves the Anthropic
    /v1/messages and OpenAI Responses /v1/responses endpoints (#240).
  * Changed: the B=1 MTP speculative-burst default is chosen per hardware.
    Batch-capable targets default on only on M5-class hardware with a neural
    accelerator (M1 Ultra regressed); non-batchable targets stay always-on;
    MLXCEL_ENABLE_MTP_B1 overrides either way (#216).
  * Changed: partially matched paged prefixes are adopted instead of
    declined, and paged adoption clones and pins shared blocks rather than
    consuming them (#230, #232).
  * Changed: vendored MLX bumped to upstream main (2026-06-11); the steel
    GEMM overlay was retired (#223).
  * Perf: chunked slab storage for the paged pool, presized per prefill
    span with eager slab eval, plus per-frame decode token streaming from
    the disaggregated decode role (#237, #229, #214).
  * Fix: per-row position holes broke B>1 batched MTP greedy parity after
    divergent accepts; the surviving K/V is now compacted to each row's
    accepted end with per-row RoPE and a precise mask (#211).
  * Fix: guard empty-batch paged-decode fallbacks and use absolute block
    indexing so a logical_start > 0 write addresses the correct block
    (#215).
  * Fix: support chunked-prefill prompts in the disaggregated serving
    handoff, with a 1M-token admission cap and pool release on extract
    error (#213).
  * Fix: apply the chat stream filter to disaggregated router output (#212);
    finish a chunked prefill when the first chunk reaches the prompt end
    (#179).
  * Fix: release paged KV block pins on prompt-cache evict or decline,
    closing a pre-existing leak of the origin allocation (#170); account
    real paged pool bytes in the cache ledger and stats (#231).
  * Fix: enforce the pack3 size contracts in release builds (#236).
  * Fix: render assistant tool_calls.arguments as a JSON object on
    multi-turn (#210); render the request's tools into the prompt (#207);
    expand bare model names in the download subcommand (#177).
  * Security: harden the paged KV handoff deserialization boundary (frame
    cap, geometry anchor, per-layer consistency, empty-sequence rejection),
    and release already-taken blocks on a partial restore failure (#186).
  * Docs: new docs/CONTINUOUS_BATCHING.md and an expanded unified-cache
    section in docs/turbo-kv-cache.md (#194).
  * Chore: record upstream attribution for ported third-party code (#238);
    bump the minor-and-patch dependency group with 3 updates (#180).

