mlxcel (0.1.3-1~jammy1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Changed (BREAKING): `mlxcel list` now lists local downloaded models by
    default; the supported-architecture catalog moved to the new `mlxcel arch`
    verb (alias `mlxcel supported`), and the `mlxcel list --local` flag was
    removed (clap rejects it). Migration: use `mlxcel arch` for the catalog and
    drop `--local`, since the bare `mlxcel list` now does the same thing (#138).
  * Added: `mlxcel list` output redesign. The default table is now NAME / SIZE /
    MODIFIED (a relative time from the snapshot directory mtime); the absolute
    path moved behind `-v` / `--verbose`. New `--json` (stable array), `-q` /
    `--quiet` (repo-ids only), and `--sort name|size|modified` modes; the header
    contracts `$HOME` to `~` and dims secondary columns on a TTY, respecting
    `NO_COLOR` (#141).
  * Fixed (security): chat-template rendering is bounded with minijinja fuel (a
    50M-instruction cap) so a pathological model template can no longer cause a
    denial of service. Exhaustion returns a clean `OutOfFuel` error instead of
    panicking, and real templates run far under the cap (#129, PR #139).
  * Fixed: the base-model warning no longer presents `-it` as a universal
    instruction-tuned suffix; it now names the per-family conventions (Gemma
    `-it`; Llama and Qwen2.5 `-Instruct`; Qwen3 and Qwen3.5 plain name vs.
    `-Base`) (#137).

 -- Jeongkyu Shin <inureyes@gmail.com>  Sat, 30 May 2026 16:30:00 +0900

mlxcel (0.1.2-1~jammy1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Fix: when `tokenizer_config.json` ships no `chat_template` field
    and there is no `chat_template.jinja`, the chat fallback path no
    longer collapses into echo loops on base / non-instruction-tuned
    models. Previously `render_prompt` called `concat_plaintext`,
    which is bare content-only concatenation with no role markers,
    so a base completion model took the most natural continuation
    of an unstructured prompt and parroted the user's last turn
    indefinitely. The implicit "no template found" path now uses a
    generic `User: ... Assistant: ...` pseudo-template via
    `concat_userassistant_fallback`, with a trailing `Assistant:`
    cue (no newline) that nudges the model to produce an assistant
    turn next instead of completing its own prompt with another
    `User:` line. The `processor.is_none()` warning still fires and
    still recommends the `-it` Hub counterpart; the explicit
    `--no-chat-template` flag is unchanged and remains the offline
    `mlxcel generate --no-chat-template` parallel for raw,
    completion-style concatenation. Template-render failure inside
    the chat-template path now falls back to the structured form
    as well, rather than raw concat. Unknown roles such as `tool`
    are preserved verbatim with the same `Role: ` pattern instead
    of silently merging into the prior turn (#133, PR #136)

