    `-p` now streams a chat session token-by-token, preserves
    conversation context across turns, and supports `/bye`, `/clear`,
    and `/?` slash commands plus `"""` multiline blocks (#101)
  * Added: local model management. `mlxcel list --local` lists
    downloaded snapshots with on-disk size and absolute path;
    `mlxcel rm <repo-id>` deletes from the mlxcel store and reports
    freed bytes, prompts on TTY, requires `--yes` on non-TTY, and
    refuses to touch the read-only HuggingFace cache (#99)
  * Added: repo-id-aware `-m/--model` across `generate`, `serve`,
    `inspect`, `mlxcel-server`, and `run`. An `owner/name` repo-id is
    resolved against legacy `./models/<name>`, HF cache,
